<p>We’ll return back to these keys later.</p>
<p>Opening a new frame (aka GUI window) can be achieved with the function <code>other-frame-prefix</code>. We can wrap this function so that any interactive command can be invoked in a new frame as shown below.</p>
<div class="highlight"><table class="highlighttable"><tr><td class="linenos"><div class="linenodiv"><pre><span class="normal">1</span>
<span class="normal">2</span>
<span class="normal">3</span>
<span class="normal">4</span>
<span class="normal">5</span></pre></div></td><td class="code"><div><pre><span></span><code><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">defun</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nv">cc/--command-in-new-frame</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">cmd</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="w">  </span><span class="s">&quot;Invoke CMD in a new frame.</span>
<span class="s">This command creates a new frame populated by CMD.&quot;</span>
<span class="w">  </span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">other-frame-prefix</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="w">  </span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nf">call-interactively</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nv">cmd</span><span class="p">))</span>
</code></pre></div></td></tr></table></div>

